Functions:
-- we can use the code multiple times without the need of writing the same code using functions
-- A function is a reusable block of code 
-- it can be called anywhere in the program
---Resuable Code: refers to the using an existing code without writing it multiple times

-- we use paramerters while using a function.. Parameters are the values(variables) which 
   are declared inside the ()

--Arguments: values which are assed through the paramerters 

Eg1:
    <script>
        function greet(){
            document.write("Hello world!")
        }
        greet()
        
    </script>
    O/P:
    Hello world!

eg2: function with paramerters:
    <script>
        function g(name){
            document.write("Hello "+name)
        }
        let name = prompt("Enter your name: ")
        g(name)
    </script>
    Eg:
    Hello mani

eg3: with arguments:
    <script>
        function add(a,b){
            document.write(a+b,"<br>");
        }
        add(3,5);
        add(7,3);

    </script>

    O/P:
    8
    10

--Function return:
-The return Statement cn be used to returm the value to a function call
eg:
    <script>
        function a(a,b){
            return (a+b);
        }
        let n1 = parseFloat(prompt("enter a number1: "))
        let n2 = parseFloat(prompt("enter a number2: "))
        let result = a(n1,n2)
        document.write("Sum of the two numbers is: "+result)
    </script>

    O/p1:
    enter a number1: 3
    enter a number2: 7
    Sum of the two numbers is: 10

    o/p2:
    Sum of the two numbers of 12.2 and 10.7 is 22.9


Anonymous function:
--A function without name
--After we create a function without name and we assign it a variable

Eg:
  <script>
        sum = function(n1,n2){
            let r = n1+n2
            return r

        }
        document.write(sum(10,9))
    </script>

    O/P:
    19
